title: Sustainable Waste Image Recognition
description: Utilized Tensorflow and OpenCV to engineer an accurate image preprocessing pipeline for a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) to classify waste images as recyclable or biodegradable, Employed Conv2D layers with ReLU activation to extract spatial features, MaxPooling2D dimensionality reduction, and implemented a dense layer of sigmoid activation to output binary predictions

title: Dynamic Movie Search Engine
description: Created a robust search engine that accepts user input to efficiently search for and retrieve information about movies, studios, and ratings; Supports multi-keyword searches, delivering both intersection and individual results for an enhanced and more comprehensive user experience; Implements several distinct data structures to optimize search functionality and improve performance

title: Septic Patient Analysis
description: Proficiently implemented data wrangling and data standardization on a database containing 10,000+ dataframes with over 250 rows each, handling discrepancies, missing values, then generated several data visualizations to display multifaceted insights relating to differences in physiological characteristics between septic and nonseptic patients; Conducted numerous statistical analysis tests, PCA analysis, and KDE comparisons to uncover significant findings about correlations between physiological feature patterns/trends and sepsis diagnosis
